  // Social: "More than 43 million people living in the United States today were born in another country — and almost every tech guide online assumes you've already been here for decades. This plain-English guide is written for newcomers: how to get a US phone number without a credit check, open a bank account without an SSN, send money home affordably, find work online, learn English for free, stay connected with family, and avoid scams that specifically target immigrants. Welcome."
  // Newsletter: "Whether you arrived last week or last year, moving to a new country is one of the biggest changes a person can go through — and technology can either be a huge help or one more thing to struggle with. This guide covers the essentials: prepaid phone plans that don't require credit or a Social Security number, translation apps that genuinely work in real conversations, banks and fintechs that accept an ITIN, the cheapest ways to send money to family abroad, online job sites with resources in your language, messaging apps popular in the US versus the ones you may already use, free English learning tools, government websites you'll need, and the scams that target newcomers. Written warmly, in plain language, for real people and real lives. Welcome — we are glad you are here."
